com.blockwithme.util.shared.converters

Interface StringConverter<CONTEXT,E>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Converter<CONTEXT,E>, ObjectConverter<CONTEXT,E,String>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EnumStringConverter, StringConverterBase

    public interface StringConverter<CONTEXT,E>
extends ObjectConverter<CONTEXT,E,String>
    StringConverter implements the conversion of some object type, to and from Java String values. OK, String is not a primitive type, but it's still one that is normally supported in most serialization APIs.
